            <title>[LUCENE-3059] PulsingTermState.clone leaks memory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3059</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I looked at the heap dump from the OOME this morning (thank you Uwe&lt;br/&gt;
for turning this on!), and I think it&apos;s a real memory leak.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, not really a leak; rather, the cloned PulsingTermState, which we&lt;br/&gt;
cache in the terms dict cache, is hanging onto large byte[]&lt;br/&gt;
unnecessarily.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
